==Turkish==
===Etymology===
From {{inh|tr|ota|یارمق|tr=yarmak||to split, rend}}, from {{inh|tr|trk-pro|*yār-||to split}}.<ref>{{R:tut-pro:SDM|*jār-|url=http://starling.rinet.ru/cgi-bin/response.cgi?single=1&basename=%2fdata%2falt%2fturcet&text_number=1425&root=config}}</ref> Akin to {{cog|xgn-pro|*jara-||to split open, open wide}} ({{cog|mn|ярах||to cleave, thrust, draw open}}).
{{rel-top|cognates}}
Cognate with {{cog|oui||tr=yar-||to split, divide}}, {{cog|xqa||tr=yarmāk||to split, cleave, divide}}, {{cog|az|yarmaq||to cut through}}, {{cog|ba|ярыу||to split}}, {{cog|chg||tr=yarmaq|t=to split}}, {{cog|cv|ҫур||to cut, split}}, {{cog|kk|жару||to split}}, {{cog|kjh|чарарға||to split, divide}}, {{cog|ky|жаруу||to split}}, {{cog|alt|јарар||to cut, hack, split}}, {{cog|tt|яру||to split}}, {{cog|tk|ýarmak|ýārmak|t=to cut up}}, {{cog|tyv|чарар||to split}}, {{cog|ug|يارماق||to split}}, {{cog|uz|yormoq||to split}}, {{cog|sah|саркаах||split (adj.)}}.
{{rel-bottom}}
